-- BofA Merrill Unit Sells $140 Million in Lehman Claims to Investor Varde
-- B y   L i n d a   S a n d l e r
-- 2010-10-05T18:15:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/merrill-sells-140-million-in-lehman-claims-to-investor-varde.html
A Merrill Lynch & Co. unit sold 
$140 million in claims on bankrupt Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc.
to Varde Investment Partners LP of Minneapolis, according to
court filings. The price wasn’t disclosed.  The claims were part of a $350 million Lehman holding that
Merrill, owned by Bank of America Corp., bought from the Federal
Home Loan Bank of Atlanta, according to today’s filings in U.S.
Bankruptcy Court in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Linda Sandler in New York at 
